the Coq proof assistant is the inclusion of a conversion rule in its logical

valid as part of the proof objects, their size soon becomes prohibitively
large. It has been argued that such arguments should not be recorded in formal
proofs but rather should be automatically decided through computation M-bM-^@M-^S a
